\begin{definition} \label{def:martindigraph} Let $G$ be a $4$-regular graph. The \emph{Martin polynomial of $G$} is

text:
\begin{equation*}
            q(G) = q(G \setminus a;x,y) + (x-1)q(G * a \setminus a;x,y), and
        \end{equation*}

