    \item $q(E_n;x,y) = y^n$.
\end{enumerate}
\end{theorem}

Lastly, note that while the single-variable interlace polynomial can be viewed as a specialization of the restricted Tutte-Martin polynomial of an isotropic system (see Section \ref{sec:isotropic} below), no such generalization is known for the two-variable version.

